subSubSection.paragraph:
Micromys cingulatus
Storch & Dahlmann, 1995

from Maramena (Miocene/Pliocene boundary of 
Greece
) is similar in size to 

M. bendai

from MCC, but it exhibits less roots in M1 (three roots plus an extremely rare incipient fourth central rootlet), a reduced t7 and lacks the t1 bis in M2 (
Storch & Dahlmann 1995
).
